{"componentChunkName":"component---src-pages-blog-details-js","path":"/blog/customize-the-browser-context-menu-in-your-next-react-app","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<h1>Customize the browser Context-menu in your next ReactÂ app</h1>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 1000px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/d0b9f94fb15ea5e2c117c5b15a23afcf/e5166/1_EjGuQ4n3brH0-NLJT5C0QA.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 74.8%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"rctx-contextmenu\"\n        title=\"Photo by Ivan Bandura / @unstable_affliction / Unsplash\"\n        src=\"/static/d0b9f94fb15ea5e2c117c5b15a23afcf/a2510/1_EjGuQ4n3brH0-NLJT5C0QA.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/d0b9f94fb15ea5e2c117c5b15a23afcf/0479a/1_EjGuQ4n3brH0-NLJT5C0QA.jpg 250w,\n/static/d0b9f94fb15ea5e2c117c5b15a23afcf/41099/1_EjGuQ4n3brH0-NLJT5C0QA.jpg 500w,\n/static/d0b9f94fb15ea5e2c117c5b15a23afcf/a2510/1_EjGuQ4n3brH0-NLJT5C0QA.jpg 1000w,\n/static/d0b9f94fb15ea5e2c117c5b15a23afcf/e5166/1_EjGuQ4n3brH0-NLJT5C0QA.jpg 1200w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span>\n<em>Photo by Ivan Bandura / @unstable_affliction / Unsplash</em></p>\n<p>Have you ever thought of customizing native Browser Context-menu like whenever a user will right-click on any specific element you want some more options to be visible in the Context-menu? OK, that's not possible to add options or even remove options from Browser's native Context-menu. In that case, you have to use Javascript to customize the Context-menu. But that's a lot of tasks. Because you have to achieve the exact look and feel also with the Context-menu feature. Below are the things which you might need to take care if you want to use your JS code to handle the Context-menu</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Should appear on right-click</li>\n<li>Should appear in the mouse position of right-clicking</li>\n<li>Should hide on outside click of the trigger area</li>\n<li>Should have an option to show sub-menus</li>\n<li>And lastly styling part</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Don't you think it's huge task for you to take care of all these things when there is a tide deadline?</p>\n<hr>\n<p>Here comes react <a href=\"https://www.npmjs.com/package/rctx-contextmenu\">rctx-contextmenu</a> plugin in the place. So we will see how we can achieve all these things without much headache in our React application.</p>\n<p>So there is an npm package called <a href=\"https://www.npmjs.com/package/rctx-contextmenu\">rctx-contextmenu</a> which solves Context-menu pain very easily. You have to just follow a few steps and you are in.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.npmjs.com/package/rctx-contextmenu\">https://www.npmjs.com/package/rctx-contextmenu</a></p>\n<h2>Installation</h2>\n<p>Run the below command to install the package first.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">npm install rctx-contextmenu</code></pre></div>\n<h2>Usage</h2>\n<p>As the plugin says, in the following, there is a very basic usage code which we can use to get started</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 800px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/95326a0e8ea3c3b43cde0a2877747a85/5a190/1_8jspEQoaDqZPJXf67-ITdA.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 80%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"rctx-contextmenu\"\n        title=\"rctx-contextmenu\"\n        src=\"/static/95326a0e8ea3c3b43cde0a2877747a85/5a190/1_8jspEQoaDqZPJXf67-ITdA.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/95326a0e8ea3c3b43cde0a2877747a85/63868/1_8jspEQoaDqZPJXf67-ITdA.png 250w,\n/static/95326a0e8ea3c3b43cde0a2877747a85/0b533/1_8jspEQoaDqZPJXf67-ITdA.png 500w,\n/static/95326a0e8ea3c3b43cde0a2877747a85/5a190/1_8jspEQoaDqZPJXf67-ITdA.png 800w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>There is a lot of other APIs which this plugin offers. So I will try to explain the above code first and then will dig deep.</p>\n<p>First of all, we are importing required packages like <a href=\"https://reactjs.org/\">React</a> and <a href=\"https://www.npmjs.com/package/rctx-contextmenu\">rctx-contextmenu</a></p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 800px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/55900c8578b2301913777b7adb7a53da/5a190/1_QX6lvIS9qSljx91Z9o15wA.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 23.2%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"rctx-contextmenu\"\n        title=\"rctx-contextmenu\"\n        src=\"/static/55900c8578b2301913777b7adb7a53da/5a190/1_QX6lvIS9qSljx91Z9o15wA.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/55900c8578b2301913777b7adb7a53da/63868/1_QX6lvIS9qSljx91Z9o15wA.png 250w,\n/static/55900c8578b2301913777b7adb7a53da/0b533/1_QX6lvIS9qSljx91Z9o15wA.png 500w,\n/static/55900c8578b2301913777b7adb7a53da/5a190/1_QX6lvIS9qSljx91Z9o15wA.png 800w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>Then, we are creating the <code class=\"language-text\">App</code> component and inside the <code class=\"language-text\">App</code> component there is two main components that are actually performing the Context-menu logic. One is <code class=\"language-text\">&lt;ContextMenuTrigger /&gt;</code> and another one is <code class=\"language-text\">&lt;ContextMenu /&gt;</code>.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 800px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/ab22fd327a1de985f1218c1cafb75bc3/5a190/1_Ba5x436q8ZBDmX9DrPCvZw.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 92.4%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"rctx-contextmenu\"\n        title=\"rctx-contextmenu\"\n        src=\"/static/ab22fd327a1de985f1218c1cafb75bc3/5a190/1_Ba5x436q8ZBDmX9DrPCvZw.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/ab22fd327a1de985f1218c1cafb75bc3/63868/1_Ba5x436q8ZBDmX9DrPCvZw.png 250w,\n/static/ab22fd327a1de985f1218c1cafb75bc3/0b533/1_Ba5x436q8ZBDmX9DrPCvZw.png 500w,\n/static/ab22fd327a1de985f1218c1cafb75bc3/5a190/1_Ba5x436q8ZBDmX9DrPCvZw.png 800w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>There is a very essential option we will talk about is id. So the <code class=\"language-text\">&lt;ContextMenu /&gt;</code> and <code class=\"language-text\">&lt;ContextMenuTrigger /&gt;</code> component's id should match to work the plugin as we want.</p>\n<p>Will come to the individual component explanation now.</p>\n<hr>\n<h3><code class=\"language-text\">&lt;ContextMenuTrigger /&gt;</code></h3>\n<p>This component actually holds the trigger area or the right-click area. We can put any kind of element inside this component as per your requirement.</p>\n<h3><code class=\"language-text\">&lt;ContextMenu /&gt;</code></h3>\n<p>This component is responsible for Context-menu items.</p>\n<h3><code class=\"language-text\">&lt;ContextMenuItem /&gt;</code></h3>\n<p>This component is responsible for each option of Context-menu. We can put any element as a child of this component.</p>\n<hr>\n<p>Now coming to  Sub-menus. <code class=\"language-text\">rctx-contextmenu</code> Also supports sub-menus. For that, there is another component we have to use that is <code class=\"language-text\">&lt;Submenu /&gt;</code>. Following is the code which includes sub-menus. To add <code class=\"language-text\">&lt;Submenu /&gt;</code> we have to import <code class=\"language-text\">Submenu</code> component from <code class=\"language-text\">rctx-contextmenu</code> first. Then we can use it as the following piece of code shows.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 800px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/4690e2d011c817e2f8ba0cb96ab5f322/5a190/1_eDp-MdWwuQR1n7eGCAJZ7A.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 106.4%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"rctx-contextmenu\"\n        title=\"rctx-contextmenu\"\n        src=\"/static/4690e2d011c817e2f8ba0cb96ab5f322/5a190/1_eDp-MdWwuQR1n7eGCAJZ7A.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/4690e2d011c817e2f8ba0cb96ab5f322/63868/1_eDp-MdWwuQR1n7eGCAJZ7A.png 250w,\n/static/4690e2d011c817e2f8ba0cb96ab5f322/0b533/1_eDp-MdWwuQR1n7eGCAJZ7A.png 500w,\n/static/4690e2d011c817e2f8ba0cb96ab5f322/5a190/1_eDp-MdWwuQR1n7eGCAJZ7A.png 800w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>There is a lot of other APIs which we can use. I would suggest go the <a href=\"https://www.npmjs.com/package/rctx-contextmenu\">official package page</a> or the <a href=\"https://github.com/reachtokish/rctx-contextmenu\">GitHub repo</a> and explore all the options.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://github.com/reachtokish/rctx-contextmenu\">https://github.com/reachtokish/rctx-contextmenu</a></p>\n<h2>Conclusion</h2>\n<p>I think we have covered pretty much very basic features but there is a lot of other features that you can explore from the official plugin page.</p>\n<p>I hope you have liked my first ever blog. If you have really liked it please do clap and share it publicly. Thanks for reading, it means a lot to me!</p>","frontmatter":{"date":"April 24, 2020","slug":"/blog/customize-the-browser-context-menu-in-your-next-react-app","title":"Customize the browser Context-menu in your next ReactÂ app"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/blog/customize-the-browser-context-menu-in-your-next-react-app","prev":null,"next":{"frontmatter":{"slug":"/blog/deep-dive-into-css-variable","title":"Deep dive into CSS variable"}}}}}